"n.仪器，设备 【英】 n. 仪器,设备(set of instruments in scientific experiments) 【例】 laboratory apparatus n. 器械, 设备, 仪器 【例】There is sports apparatus in the gym 体育馆里有体育器材. 【记】1)来自拉丁语apparere, ap- = ad-添加, parare准备, 为别的事情作准备－机械2)appa读: 我怕, rat老鼠, us我们. 我怕老鼠吃我们－所以我们要用一些仪器设备, 譬如捕鼠器. 【记】源自prepare 准备仪器；parts 零件；音：operator 操作的东西→器械 apparatus (n.)  1620s, from Latin apparatus ""tools, implements, equipment; preparation, a preparing,"" noun of state from past participle stem of apparare ""prepare,"" from ad- ""to"" (see ad-) + parare ""make ready"" (see pare)."
